
Overview of noun share

The noun share has 5 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (29) share, portion, part, percentage -- (assets belonging to or due to or contributed by an individual person or group; "he wanted his share in cash")
2. (12) share -- (any of the equal portions into which the capital stock of a corporation is divided and ownership of which is evidenced by a stock certificate; "he bought 100 shares of IBM at the market price")
3. (3) parcel, portion, share -- (the allotment of some amount by dividing something; "death gets more than its share of attention from theologians")
4. (3) contribution, part, share -- (the part played by a person in bringing about a result; "I am proud of my contribution in advancing the project"; "they all did their share of the work")
5. plowshare, ploughshare, share -- (a sharp steel wedge that cuts loose the top layer of soil)

Overview of verb share

The verb share has 5 senses (first 5 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (23) share -- (have in common; "Our children share a love of music"; "The two countries share a long border")
2. (19) share -- (use jointly or in common)
3. (15) partake, share, partake in -- (have, give, or receive a share of; "We shared the cake")
4. (4) share, divvy up, portion out, apportion, deal -- (give out as one's portion or share)
5. (1) share -- (communicate; "I'd like to share this idea with you")
